In [3]:
# Function of plot confusion matrix
def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, classes,
                          normalize=False,
                          title='Confusion matrix',
                          cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(classes))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, classes, rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, classes)

    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]), range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j, i, cm[i, j],
                 horizontalalignment="center",
                 color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')

importances = CBC.feature_importances_
# Sort feature importances in descending order
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]

# Rearrange feature names so they match the sorted feature importances
names = [x_train.columns[i] for i in indices]

# Create plot
plt.figure()

# Create plot title
plt.title("Catboost Classifier Feature Importance")

# Add bars
plt.barh(range(x_train.shape[1]), importances[indices])

# Add feature names as x-axis labels
plt.yticks(range(x_train.shape[1]), names, rotation=0)

# Show plot
plt.show()

importances = CBC.feature_importances_
# Sort feature importances in descending order
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]

# Rearrange feature names so they match the sorted feature importances
names = [x_train.columns[i] for i in indices]

# Create plot

# Create plot title
plt.title("Catboost Classifier Feature Importance")

# Add bars
plt.barh(range(x_train.shape[1]), importances[indices])

# Add feature names as x-axis labels
plt.yticks(range(x_train.shape[1]), names, rotation=0)

# Show plot
plt.show()

df = pd.read_csv('Churn_Modelling.csv', delimiter=',')
df = df.drop(["RowNumber", "CustomerId", "Surname"], axis = 1)
#排除特定行
ex_list = list(df)
ex_list.remove('Exited')
x, y = df[ex_list], df['Exited']
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=0)
In [64]:

x_test_ext = pd.concat([x_test_rfc,x_test],axis=1)
x_test_ext.columns = ['tree_' + str(name) if type(name) is int else name for name in x_test_ext.columns]

labelencoder = LabelEncoder()

    df[i] = labelencoder.fit_transform(df[i])

# Sort feature importances in descending order
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]

# Rearrange feature names so they match the sorted feature importances
names = [x_train_ext.columns[i] for i in indices]

# Create plot

plt.barh(range(x_train_ext.shape[1]), importances[indices])

# Add feature names as x-axis labels

importances = CBC.feature_importances_
# Sort feature importances in descending order
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]

# Rearrange feature names so they match the sorted feature importances
names = [x_train_merge.columns[i] for i in indices]

# Create plot
plt.figure()

# Create plot title
plt.title("Catboost Classifier Feature Importance")

# Add bars
plt.barh(range(x_train_merge.shape[1]), importances[indices])

# Add feature names as x-axis labels
plt.yticks(range(x_train_merge.shape[1]), names, rotation=0)

# Show plot
plt.show()
